102
00:06:11,171 --> 00:06:14,373
 narrator: animal horns are made
 from meat-industry by-products.

103
00:06:14,375 --> 00:06:16,508
       they can be shaped       
         and cut easily,        

104
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:19,311
         while remaining        
       incredibly durable.      

105
00:06:19,313 --> 00:06:23,782
 in the 20th century, synthetic 
 plastics largely replaced horn,

106
00:06:23,784 --> 00:06:26,051
           but today,           
     it's making a comeback     

107
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:31,123
        as an all-natural       
     biodegradable material.    

108
00:06:31,125 --> 00:06:36,395
   in 1749, this manufacturer   
    made inexpensive utensils   

109
00:06:36,397 --> 00:06:38,330
  for people on a tight budget. 

110
00:06:38,332 --> 00:06:40,332
 two and a half centuries later,

111
00:06:40,334 --> 00:06:43,669
          horn products         
   are desirable luxury items.  

112
00:06:43,671 --> 00:06:46,939
 this facility sources its horns
          from nigeria          

113
00:06:46,941 --> 00:06:49,608
  where ankole cattle are known 
         for their long,        

114
00:06:49,610 --> 00:06:51,677
       magnificent horns.       

115
00:06:51,679 --> 00:06:54,680
   a craftsman cuts the horns   
         on a band saw.         

116
00:06:54,682 --> 00:06:57,216
  horn is formed from keratin,  

117
00:06:57,218 --> 00:07:00,019
        the same material       
       in hair and nails.       

118
00:07:00,021 --> 00:07:02,554
     even though it's hard,     
        woodworking tools       

119
00:07:02,556 --> 00:07:05,223
    can easily cut and shape    
            the horn.           

120
00:07:05,225 --> 00:07:08,560
 the horn is also biodegradable.

121
00:07:08,562 --> 00:07:12,298
  the craftsman uses a sanding  
    disk to shape the edges.    

122
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:16,035
this particular horn will become
         a drinking mug.        

123
00:07:16,037 --> 00:07:18,169
     horn is thermoplastic.     

124
00:07:18,171 --> 00:07:20,105
  it can be shaped when heated  

125
00:07:20,107 --> 00:07:23,175
  and will retain its new shape 
          when cooled.          

126
00:07:23,177 --> 00:07:28,047
 an artisan heats a thin section
       and bends the tip.       

127
00:07:28,049 --> 00:07:31,984
  he heats the base of the thin 
   section over an open flame   

128
00:07:31,986 --> 00:07:34,185
and then carefully folds it over

129
00:07:34,187 --> 00:07:35,788
    to form a perfect handle    
          for the mug.          

130
00:07:35,790 --> 00:07:38,189
                     ♪          

131
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:40,626
   the craftsman puts the mug   
           into a vice          

132
00:07:40,628 --> 00:07:43,795
   to ensures that the handle   
    will retain its new shape   

133
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:45,397
          once cooled.          

134
00:07:45,399 --> 00:07:48,334
      in just a few steps,      
        this cattle horn        

135
00:07:48,336 --> 00:07:53,939
      has been transformed      
into a unique mug-shaped object.

136
00:07:53,941 --> 00:07:56,541
   now the mug needs a bottom.  

137
00:07:56,543 --> 00:08:00,279
a technician glues a set of mugs
        to wooden planks        

138
00:08:00,281 --> 00:08:04,683
  and then pours in a food-safe 
resin to form a watertight seal.

139
00:08:04,685 --> 00:08:07,019
                     ♪          

140
00:08:07,021 --> 00:08:10,755
        it takes 24 hours       
     for the resin to cure.     

141
00:08:10,757 --> 00:08:15,693
  once cured, a craftsman uses  
a band saw to separate the mugs.

142
00:08:15,695 --> 00:08:17,229
     then he trims the wood     

143
00:08:17,231 --> 00:08:20,232
   until there's only a small   
  amount left around the edges. 

144
00:08:20,234 --> 00:08:27,572
                     ♪          

145
00:08:27,574 --> 00:08:30,976
 the sanding disk easily removes
           the excess           

146
00:08:30,978 --> 00:08:33,512
         until the wood         
     is even with the horn.     

147
00:08:33,514 --> 00:08:38,650
                     ♪          

148
00:08:38,652 --> 00:08:41,453
       a specialized wheel      
      with sandpaper edges      

149
00:08:41,455 --> 00:08:45,857
  smoothes hard-to-reach areas  
           of the mug.          

150
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:49,127
        a craftsman sands       
and polishes each mug thoroughly

151
00:08:49,129 --> 00:08:52,130
        until they shine.       

152
00:08:52,132 --> 00:08:54,532
        for constructing        
    other types of products,    

153
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:56,735
       this facility uses       
          a deep fryer          

154
00:08:56,737 --> 00:09:01,940
    to heat sections of horn    
   in 392-degree cooking oil.   

155
00:09:01,942 --> 00:09:04,876
   a hydraulic press flattens   
       the heated material      

156
00:09:04,878 --> 00:09:08,546
      by applying pressure,     
  then it's set aside to cool.  

157
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:12,350
   after 10 minutes, the horn   
   will retain its new shape,   

158
00:09:12,352 --> 00:09:14,285
    which is called a plate.    

159
00:09:14,287 --> 00:09:17,956
     flat horn plate is used    
 to make a variety of products. 

160
00:09:17,958 --> 00:09:21,760
   here, a cutting form stamps  
           out spoons.          

161
00:09:21,762 --> 00:09:26,098
   artisans use a sanding disk  
  to refine the spoon's shape.  

162
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:29,634
    another press hollows out   
      the end of the spoon.     

163
00:09:29,636 --> 00:09:32,304
       horn is a naturally      
       non-stick material       

164
00:09:32,306 --> 00:09:36,641
     that won't absorb odor     
       or color from food.      

165
00:09:36,643 --> 00:09:39,244
        beside their many       
         other products,        

166
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:43,715
       this facility also       
     manufactures shoehorns.    

167
00:09:43,717 --> 00:09:47,052
    shoehorns get their name    
     from the horn material     

168
00:09:47,054 --> 00:09:49,321
       used to make them.       

169
00:09:49,323 --> 00:09:53,191
     a sanding disk is used     
       to shape the horn.       

170
00:09:53,193 --> 00:09:54,859
     it takes artisans years    

171
00:09:54,861 --> 00:09:59,130
           to develop           
 this particular set of skills. 

172
00:09:59,132 --> 00:10:00,865
    the horn, which has been    
          straightened          

173
00:10:00,867 --> 00:10:02,734
     in a specialized press     

174
00:10:02,736 --> 00:10:06,071
          is now ready          
      for the final phase.      

175
00:10:06,073 --> 00:10:08,807
       a craftsman refines      
      the shape of the horn     

176
00:10:08,809 --> 00:10:10,809
  by using a specialized tool,  

177
00:10:10,811 --> 00:10:14,813
   equipped with a narrow belt  
          of sandpaper          

178
00:10:14,815 --> 00:10:17,416
   he smoothes the inner curve  
         of the shoehorn        

179
00:10:17,418 --> 00:10:21,286
         by pressing on         
       the sandpaper belt.      

180
00:10:21,288 --> 00:10:24,690
 this operation requires a high 
     degree of concentration    

181
00:10:24,692 --> 00:10:26,158
           and skill.           

182
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:29,160
  too much pressure will remove 
    more of the horn material   

183
00:10:29,162 --> 00:10:33,232
         than necessary.        

184
00:10:33,234 --> 00:10:37,169
      polishing wheels give     
  the shoehorn its final sheen. 

185
00:10:37,171 --> 00:10:43,308
   once polishing is complete,  
  the horn's color is revealed. 

186
00:10:43,310 --> 00:10:46,044
      the colors of a horn      
      are near the surface,     

187
00:10:46,046 --> 00:10:52,918
  so the sander must be careful 
not to remove too much material.

188
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:56,255
      skilled craftsmanship     
   has transformed a raw horn   

189
00:10:56,257 --> 00:11:00,592
        into a shoe horn        
      in just a few steps.      

190
00:11:00,594 --> 00:11:04,062
    a laser engraving machine   
       brands the shoehorn      

191
00:11:04,064 --> 00:11:10,002
  with the manufacturer's mark. 

192
00:11:10,004 --> 00:11:12,471
          horns may be          
      an ancient material,      

193
00:11:12,473 --> 00:11:15,974
  but they still make relevant  
  instruments for modern life.  

194
00:11:23,350 --> 00:11:28,753
                     ♪          

195
00:11:28,755 --> 00:11:31,623
   narrator: many professional  
race-car drivers got their start

196
00:11:31,625 --> 00:11:34,893
       in a formula f car,      
    an entry-level racing car   

197
00:11:34,895 --> 00:11:37,763
      developed in britain      
          in the 1960s.         

198
00:11:37,765 --> 00:11:40,031
initially called "formula ford,"

199
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:42,434
      the name was changed      
          to formula f          

200
00:11:42,436 --> 00:11:45,437
          when a motor          
other than a ford was permitted.

201
00:11:47,708 --> 00:11:50,909
                     ♪          

202
00:11:50,911 --> 00:11:54,913
a formula f racecar is driven by
   both aspiring professionals  

203
00:11:54,915 --> 00:11:56,848
          and amateurs.         

204
00:11:56,850 --> 00:11:59,851
    this car can give drivers   
      a start in the sport      

205
00:11:59,853 --> 00:12:02,921
 and hopefully a strong finish. 

206
00:12:02,923 --> 00:12:05,924
       productions starts       
   with a steel tube skeleton   

207
00:12:05,926 --> 00:12:07,793
     known as a space frame.    

208
00:12:07,795 --> 00:12:11,863
      the frame is designed     
  to be lightweight yet rigid.  

209
00:12:11,865 --> 00:12:16,868
     the technician measures    
 a piece of steel to be trimmed.

210
00:12:16,870 --> 00:12:21,873
  using a band saw, he cuts the 
 steel to its specified length. 

211
00:12:21,875 --> 00:12:24,276
     this piece will be used    
       for the roll hoop,       

212
00:12:24,278 --> 00:12:29,013
which protects the driver's head
   in the event the car rolls.  

213
00:12:29,015 --> 00:12:31,816
     he measures the tubing     
         one last time.         

214
00:12:31,818 --> 00:12:33,885
         when satisfied         
       with its placement,      

215
00:12:33,887 --> 00:12:38,957
        he lowers the saw       
 and cuts off any excess steel. 

216
00:12:38,959 --> 00:12:42,427
      he clamps the tubing      
 in a hydraulic bending device. 

217
00:12:42,429 --> 00:12:44,696
                     ♪          

218
00:12:44,698 --> 00:12:48,767
once activated, the device wraps
     the tubing around a dye    

219
00:12:48,769 --> 00:12:51,770
           forming it           
    to the desired curvature.   

220
00:12:51,772 --> 00:12:54,906
         next, he builds        
    the car's front bulkhead.   

221
00:12:54,908 --> 00:12:58,510
   he arranges steel tubing in  
    the desired configuration   

222
00:12:58,512 --> 00:13:03,248
   and clamps them to the work  
   bench to hold them steady.   

223
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,383
  using angle-measuring tools,  

224
00:13:05,385 --> 00:13:06,852
     the craftsman verifies     
        that the corners        

225
00:13:06,854 --> 00:13:11,189
    of the bulkhead structure   
       measure 90 degrees.      

226
00:13:11,191 --> 00:13:15,260
 this confirms that the bulkhead
      is perfectly square.      

227
00:13:15,262 --> 00:13:20,465
  next, the bulkhead structure  
    is welded at the joints.    

228
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:24,136
 the space-frame tubing is made 
   up of varying thicknesses.   

229
00:13:24,138 --> 00:13:27,939
 this ensures the bulkhead steel
     is strong and protected    

230
00:13:27,941 --> 00:13:30,676
          in the event          
  there's a frontal collision.  

231
00:13:30,678 --> 00:13:35,680
he compares the newly fabricated
    bulkhead to the standard.   

232
00:13:35,682 --> 00:13:39,151
   once the frame is complete,  
    the builder applies epoxy   

233
00:13:39,153 --> 00:13:42,754
   to the base in preparation   
     for floor installation.    

234
00:13:42,756 --> 00:13:44,556
      since the steel floor     
         is substantial         

235
00:13:44,558 --> 00:13:47,526
    in thickness and weight,    
    it takes two technicians    

236
00:13:47,528 --> 00:13:51,563
   to lift it onto the epoxied  
   section of the space frame.  

237
00:13:51,565 --> 00:13:55,166
    in addition to the epoxy,   
     a craftsman uses rivets    

238
00:13:55,168 --> 00:13:57,569
       to fasten the floor      
          to the frame.         

239
00:13:57,571 --> 00:13:59,571
        the floor will be       
        the only barrier        

240
00:13:59,573 --> 00:14:03,642
       between the driver       
         and the track.         

241
00:14:03,644 --> 00:14:06,378
      with the space frame      
       and floor secured,       

242
00:14:06,380 --> 00:14:11,650
    the racecar is ready for    
 mechanical-component assembly. 

243
00:14:11,652 --> 00:14:14,586
 after installing adapter plates
         to the engine,         

244
00:14:14,588 --> 00:14:18,390
   the engine is hoisted into   
  the back of the space frame.  

245
00:14:18,392 --> 00:14:21,392
     then the adapter plates    
    are bolted to the frame,    

246
00:14:21,394 --> 00:14:24,396
  securing the engine in place. 

247
00:14:24,398 --> 00:14:25,997
   the technician uses a hoist  

248
00:14:25,999 --> 00:14:29,534
to carry the transmission system
          to the motor.         

249
00:14:29,536 --> 00:14:33,538
  once in position, he connects 
 the input shaft to the engine. 

250
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:36,675
                     ♪          

251
00:14:36,677 --> 00:14:39,611
  he straps a fire extinguisher 
      to the cockpit floor      

252
00:14:39,613 --> 00:14:43,748
       using metal bands.       

253
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:46,485
     then he runs wires from    
      the instrument panel      

254
00:14:46,487 --> 00:14:51,556
       to the extinguisher      
      for easy activation.      

255
00:14:51,558 --> 00:14:56,627
he screws the panel to the cowl.

256
00:14:56,629 --> 00:14:58,029
      moving to the front,      

257
00:14:58,031 --> 00:15:00,899
      the technician bolts      
  the foot pedals to the floor. 

258
00:15:00,901 --> 00:15:05,169
                     ♪          

259
00:15:05,171 --> 00:15:08,907
      next, he works on the     
rack-and-pinion steering system.

260
00:15:08,909 --> 00:15:10,375
   this assembly will convert   

261
00:15:10,377 --> 00:15:12,978
      the rotational motion     
      of the steering wheel     

262
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:16,648
      to the lateral motion     
          of the rack.          

263
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:21,452
     tie rods link the tires    
         to the system.         

264
00:15:21,454 --> 00:15:23,722
      the technician tests      
    the movement of the rack    

265
00:15:23,724 --> 00:15:28,659
           to confirm           
  that it's operating smoothly. 

266
00:15:28,661 --> 00:15:31,863
       at another station,      
 computerized tools drill holes 

267
00:15:31,865 --> 00:15:34,599
  in a solid piece of aluminum. 

268
00:15:34,601 --> 00:15:37,002
      this step transforms      
          the aluminum          

269
00:15:37,004 --> 00:15:39,404
       into a part called       
         the bell crank.        

270
00:15:39,406 --> 00:15:41,406
         the bell crank         
       will provide a link      

271
00:15:41,408 --> 00:15:47,679
  between the car's suspension  
  rods and the shock absorbers. 

272
00:15:47,681 --> 00:15:50,816
    it takes about 10 minutes   
  for these computerized tools  

273
00:15:50,818 --> 00:15:52,950
   to turn a piece of aluminum  

274
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:55,287
    into a precision-crafted    
           bell crank.          

275
00:15:55,289 --> 00:15:59,691
                     ♪          

276
00:15:59,693 --> 00:16:03,361
   the technician installs the  
 bell crank onto the car frame. 

277
00:16:03,363 --> 00:16:07,098
                     ♪          

278
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:09,501
    with that, they've turned   
      a production corner,      

279
00:16:09,503 --> 00:16:12,971
  and it's full speed ahead to  
   the next phase, coming up.   

280
00:16:20,714 --> 00:16:26,851
                     ♪          

281
00:16:26,853 --> 00:16:28,786
            narrator:           
   a formula f car is designed  

282
00:16:28,788 --> 00:16:32,857
    to make semi-professional   
 racing accessible to amateurs. 

283
00:16:32,859 --> 00:16:37,195
this vehicle's steel space frame
    is inexpensive to produce   

284
00:16:37,197 --> 00:16:39,998
      and easier to repair      
     in comparison to frames    

285
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,100
      made of carbon fiber.     

286
00:16:46,339 --> 00:16:48,206
  with the steel frame complete 

287
00:16:48,208 --> 00:16:50,609
         and the engine         
   and transmission installed,  

288
00:16:50,611 --> 00:16:54,012
   the technician bolts shock   
    absorbers to the chassis,   

289
00:16:54,014 --> 00:16:57,615
      one for each wheel's      
       suspension system.       

290
00:16:57,617 --> 00:17:01,219
 a technician connects the shock
  absorbers to the bell crank,  

291
00:17:01,221 --> 00:17:05,289
     linking it to the rest     
    of the suspension system.   

292
00:17:05,291 --> 00:17:10,228
    he bolts suspension arms    
     to mounts on the frame.    

293
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:13,164
    a push rod links the arms   
       to the bell crank.       

294
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:17,569
                     ♪          

295
00:17:17,571 --> 00:17:20,639
 he bolts the wheel hub assembly
     to the suspension arms.    

296
00:17:20,641 --> 00:17:23,441
                     ♪          

297
00:17:23,443 --> 00:17:26,110
   he assembles a brake rotor   
           to the hub.          

298
00:17:26,112 --> 00:17:31,716
                     ♪          

299
00:17:31,718 --> 00:17:35,253
        then he installs        
    the drive shaft assembly.   

300
00:17:35,255 --> 00:17:37,588
     this assembly connects     
        the transmission        

301
00:17:37,590 --> 00:17:41,459
        to the wheel hub.       

302
00:17:41,461 --> 00:17:45,263
   that completes the push-rod  
suspension system for one wheel.

303
00:17:45,265 --> 00:17:48,466
                     ♪          

304
00:17:48,468 --> 00:17:50,267
     this sheet of aluminum     
          will be used          

305
00:17:50,269 --> 00:17:53,672
         for the back of        
   the fuel-cell compartment.   

306
00:17:53,674 --> 00:17:56,741
 he measures and marks the sheet
          accordingly.          

307
00:17:56,743 --> 00:18:00,544
 he clamps the sheet in a press 
  brake along the measured line 

308
00:18:00,546 --> 00:18:03,080
 and activates the press brake. 

309
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:04,616
      the bend forms a flap     

310
00:18:04,618 --> 00:18:08,753
   that will be used to attach  
   the sheet to the car frame.  

311
00:18:08,755 --> 00:18:11,623
   he measures and marks spots  
       for mounting holes       

312
00:18:11,625 --> 00:18:14,292
   so they'll be evenly spaced  
          when drilled.         

313
00:18:14,294 --> 00:18:16,427
                     ♪          

314
00:18:16,429 --> 00:18:19,898
the panel is placed in the space
    frame behind the cockpit    

315
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:23,434
      with the flap resting     
       on lateral tubing.       

316
00:18:23,436 --> 00:18:27,238
    the fuel cell is made of    
 a flexible rubber-like material

317
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:31,109
   that's unlikely to rupture   
       if in an accident.       

318
00:18:31,111 --> 00:18:34,179
     he assembles the sides     
  and front panels to the back, 

319
00:18:34,181 --> 00:18:37,449
     creating a compartment     
  that encloses the fuel cell.  

320
00:18:37,451 --> 00:18:39,317
   next, the technician wires   

321
00:18:39,319 --> 00:18:42,320
the racecar's electrical systems
            together.           

322
00:18:42,322 --> 00:18:43,922
      he crimps connectors      
    to the ends of the wires    

323
00:18:43,924 --> 00:18:46,323
       and plugs them into      

324
00:18:46,325 --> 00:18:49,460
       their corresponding      
     electrical components.     

325
00:18:49,462 --> 00:18:57,235
he routes wiring through the car
  and plugs in the alternator.  

326
00:18:57,237 --> 00:19:00,805
     he installs fiberglass     
 support parts to the radiators,

327
00:19:00,807 --> 00:19:03,608
   attaching one to each side   
           of the car.          

328
00:19:03,610 --> 00:19:05,744
                     ♪          

329
00:19:05,746 --> 00:19:08,680
       he runs hoses from       
  the radiators to the engine.  

330
00:19:08,682 --> 00:19:10,148
                     ♪          

331
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:12,617
     with the radiators now     
        on the supports,        

332
00:19:12,619 --> 00:19:14,753
      the packing material      
           is removed.          

333
00:19:14,755 --> 00:19:16,621
                     ♪          

334
00:19:16,623 --> 00:19:20,492
a cone-shaped air filter located
  on the engine's throttle body 

335
00:19:20,494 --> 00:19:23,561
         will keep dirt         
       out of the engine.       

336
00:19:23,563 --> 00:19:26,164
        after installing        
     front shock absorbers,     

337
00:19:26,166 --> 00:19:29,434
he assembles the steering column
      and shaft to the car.     

338
00:19:29,436 --> 00:19:31,702
                     ♪          

339
00:19:31,704 --> 00:19:36,708
  he slides the steering wheel  
        onto the column.        

340
00:19:36,710 --> 00:19:40,511
 he tucks a special safety seat 
        into the cockpit.       

341
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:44,515
  the seat has been custom-made 
         for the driver.        

342
00:19:44,517 --> 00:19:48,786
   the harness has six straps   
   for upper-body protection.   

343
00:19:48,788 --> 00:19:51,456
                     ♪          

344
00:19:51,458 --> 00:19:54,392
then he connects an exhaust pipe
          to the engine         

345
00:19:54,394 --> 00:19:57,395
     and hangs it to the car    
        with metal bands.       

346
00:19:57,397 --> 00:20:01,666
                     ♪          

347
00:20:01,668 --> 00:20:04,469
 after the fiberglass body parts
           are molded,          

348
00:20:04,471 --> 00:20:07,071
        he maps out holes       
         for components.        

349
00:20:07,073 --> 00:20:10,608
                     ♪          

350
00:20:10,610 --> 00:20:13,945
      he cuts out the holes     
   with a rotary sanding tool.  

351
00:20:13,947 --> 00:20:15,613
                     ♪          

352
00:20:15,615 --> 00:20:18,949
    the cockpit's side panels   
  are fitted to the space frame 

353
00:20:18,951 --> 00:20:20,551
     and screwed into place.    

354
00:20:20,553 --> 00:20:23,220
                     ♪          

355
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:26,357
       the nose of the car      
    is made of carbon fiber.    

356
00:20:26,359 --> 00:20:28,493
          the strength          
       of the carbon fiber      

357
00:20:28,495 --> 00:20:30,962
       provides additional      
        crash protection.       

358
00:20:30,964 --> 00:20:34,299
                     ♪          

359
00:20:34,301 --> 00:20:37,168
  the body panels are attached  
         with fasteners         

360
00:20:37,170 --> 00:20:40,037
       that can be quickly      
         during a race.         

361
00:20:40,039 --> 00:20:43,374
                     ♪          

362
00:20:43,376 --> 00:20:45,510
    with the front suspension   
           installed,           

363
00:20:45,512 --> 00:20:48,446
          this racecar          
      is ready for wheels.      

364
00:20:48,448 --> 00:20:50,648
         the technician         
       torques the locknut      

365
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:54,985
  that holds the wheel in place 
 and slides a pin onto the axle.

366
00:20:54,987 --> 00:20:58,256
                     ♪          

367
00:20:58,258 --> 00:21:00,124
         it takes about         
       two to three months      

368
00:21:00,126 --> 00:21:02,727
            to build            
     this formula f racecar.    

369
00:21:02,729 --> 00:21:06,397
                     ♪          

370
00:21:06,399 --> 00:21:10,935
  now that it's left the shop,  
 things are sure to accelerate. 

371
00:21:10,937 --> 00:21:16,841
                     ♪          

